// Code Generation Guidelines

// 1. Technology Selection
// - Use techStack from contract.ai.json if specified
// - If not specified, choose based on:
//   - Simplicity (minimal dependencies)
//   - Project size (small = lightweight, large = robust)
//   - Entity complexity

// 2. Code Style
// - Clean, readable code
// - Minimal comments (self-documenting)
// - Consistent naming conventions
// - Error handling

// 3. API Design
// - RESTful conventions
// - Proper HTTP status codes
// - JSON responses
// - Health endpoint required

// 4. Storage
// - In-memory for prototypes
// - Database for production
// - Generated IDs (uuid or incremental)

// 5. Testing
// - E2E tests for CRUD operations
// - Health check test
// - Proper assertions
